  "notes": [
    "The Earth and Environmental Science major is for students interested in interactions between the solid Earth, Oceans, Atmosphere, the Biosphere, and Human Environments. Listed below are the lower division preparation courses for the major. To be considered for this major, you must complete the following coursework by the end of spring before transfer: One introductory course in Earth Sciences with Lab, One year of General Chemistry courses with Lab for majors, and One Calculus course. Completion of one Introductory Biology course in (Evolution) with Lab and one course in Calculus-Based Physics with Lab (Mechanics) is STRONGLY RECOMMENDED . All courses must be taken for a letter grade. For more information regarding this major and UCLA's transfer selection process, visit https:// epss.ucla.edu and https:// admission.ucla.edu . PLEASE NOTE: the community college courses listed below have been approved to satisfy the preparation required for this major at UCLA, but they may not be exact equivalents of the UCLA courses listed."
